CEZ AS, the largest Czech power
producer, said Bulgarian protests against energy bills differ
from the situation in Albania which revoked its license,
 Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing Tomas Pleskac, the head of
distribution.  Thousands of Bulgarians protested over the weekend against
higher electricity bills in the country where CEZ controls three
power distribution companies, the newspaper said. The Albanian
energy regulator revoked CEZâ€™s license in January following
